  "learn": {
    "heading": "Mixed numbers ↔ improper fractions",
    "intro": "<p>A <strong>mixed number</strong> like 1 1/2 is one whole plus a part. To make it an <strong>improper fraction</strong>: multiply the whole by the denominator, add the top, keep the bottom. To go back, see how many wholes fit.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>To improper:</strong> 1 1/2 → (1 × 2) + 1 = 3, over 2 → 3/2.",
      "<strong>Back to mixed:</strong> 5/2 → 2 wholes (4/2) with 1/2 left → 2 1/2."
    ]
  },
